, such as the stopped $R$-hadrons. But the\nresults are promising even in the case of not so heavy LLPs and/or when some of\nthe available energy is carried by a massive invisible daughter. This urges us\nto look more in details at these unusual signatures, taking into account the\nparticularities of each layer that constitutes the detector. From the\n\\textit{BMO} perspective, we review how each layer of the detector could be\nexploited and what improvements can be made to enhance the shower shapes and\nthe timing information, for instance. We also argue that the cosmic ray events,\nthe most important background, can be easily dealt with.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Jun 2017 17:21:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 7 Dec 2018 16:04:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-20"}
