cally reside in\nmerging systems over non-interacting galaxies. Our findings show that\ngalaxy-galaxy interactions do, on average, trigger luminous AGN activity\nsubstantially more often than in secularly evolving non-interacting galaxies,\nand we further suggest that the BH growth rate may be closely tied to the\ndynamical time of the merger system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Jun 2017 18:00:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 8 Dec 2017 22:34:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-10"}
