iduals from tilted ring models in the\nsimulations appear larger than in observed galaxies, our results suggest that\nnon-circular motions should be carefully taken into account when considering\nthe evidence for dark matter cores in individual galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Jun 2017 20:08:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 Apr 2018 13:14:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 20 Aug 2018 15:07:31 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 2 Nov 2018 10:39:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-05"}
